$ PowerShell: common parameter -errorAction

The value given with the parameter `-errorAction` sets the value of the
→ Windows/PowerShell/language/variable/preference[preference] variable → Windows/PowerShell/language/variable/preference/errorActionPreference[`$errorActionPreference`] in the scope of the cmdlet.
-
This value can be set to any member of the → Microsoft/dot-net/namespaces-classes/System/Management/Automation/ActionPreference[`System.Management.Automation.ActionPreference`] enum.

`-errorAction` can be a abbreviated with `-ea`.
